# 🚀 Future Enhancements

- Upload support (PUT command)
- Directory listing (LIST command)
- User authentication
- Password protection
- SSL/TLS encrypted communication
- Multi-threaded implementation using `pthread`
- Resume interrupted downloads
- File compression before transfer
- Progress indicator
- Logging and monitoring
- Support for binary files of any size
- Command-line shell with FTP-like commands (`GET`, `PUT`, `LS`, `PWD`, `QUIT`)

---

# 📈 Advantages

- Supports multiple clients simultaneously
- Lightweight implementation
- Uses standard TCP sockets
- Modular client-server architecture
- Efficient file streaming
- Demonstrates real-world networking concepts

---

# ⚠️ Limitations

- Download-only functionality
- No authentication mechanism
- No encryption of transferred data
- Linux/POSIX dependent
- Process-based concurrency may consume more resources than threads
- Limited command set

